of color in general.

01:11:17.320 --> 01:11:19.111
That's actually not
what I'm talking about.

01:11:19.111 --> 01:11:20.716
And I should say
also, in general,

01:11:20.716 --> 01:11:22.840
everything I'm going to
tell you would be an effort

01:11:22.840 --> 01:11:25.060
to remove this sort
of violence prevention

01:11:25.060 --> 01:11:27.520
from the domain of police
and move it into a broader

01:11:27.520 --> 01:11:29.830
public health or
even municipal system

01:11:29.830 --> 01:11:32.380
in which we can use
this information

01:11:32.380 --> 01:11:36.730
to divert people and services
to those who are most at risk

01:11:36.730 --> 01:11:40.360
in between those 83
days from gunshot victim

01:11:40.360 --> 01:11:41.770
to gunshot victim.

01:11:41.770 --> 01:11:44.630
And we know-- we know
stuff that works.

01:11:44.630 --> 01:11:46.330
How do we get a trauma
care specialist?

01:11:46.330 --> 01:11:48.038
How do we get a health
care professional?

01:11:48.038 --> 01:11:50.800
How do we get a priest, a
football coach, an educator,

01:11:50.800 --> 01:11:54.220
and, yes, sometimes a cop,
into those networks when

01:11:54.220 --> 01:11:55.180
they're needed?

01:11:55.180 --> 01:11:55.990
Right?

01:11:55.990 --> 01:11:58.750
So sort of a shooting-- let's
call it a monitoring system

01:11:58.750 --> 01:12:00.460
if I can't use the
word surveillance.

01:12:00.460 --> 01:12:02.740
And let me just say,
to go back to some

01:12:02.740 --> 01:12:05.680
of the comments that were made
earlier, it should be local.

01:12:05.680 --> 01:12:06.700
It should be open.

01:12:06.700 --> 01:12:09.040
And it should be
responsive, which

01:12:09.040 --> 01:12:10.710
will also help police
violence, which

01:12:10.710 --> 01:12:13.180
we'll talk about in a minute.

01:12:13.180 --> 01:12:14.290
I will tell you this.

01:12:14.290 --> 01:12:16.720
On the policing side
of things, there

01:12:16.720 --> 01:12:21.610
have been multiple studies
and systematic reviews that

01:12:21.610 --> 01:12:25.900
show you, if you have
focused policing efforts,

01:12:25.900 --> 01:12:30.580
you can actually see
gun violence reduction

01:12:30.580 --> 01:12:32.590
with fewer arrests.

01:12:32.590 --> 01:12:34.600
So if anything, when
we're talking about it's

01:12:34.600 --> 01:12:39.010
application to policing, it
is not to broaden the scope,

01:12:39.010 --> 01:12:41.530
but rather to focus the scope.

01:12:41.530 --> 01:12:43.210
When we talk about
policing, I just

01:12:43.210 --> 01:12:45.481
want to say a couple of things.

01:12:45.481 --> 01:12:47.230
Do you know we actually
had another period

01:12:47.230 --> 01:12:49.990
in this country when we reduced
police-involved shootings

01:12:49.990 --> 01:12:51.610
by more than 50%?

01:12:51.610 --> 01:12:54.790
Does anybody know when that was?

01:12:54.790 --> 01:12:56.950
It was in the late
'60s, early '70s--

01:12:56.950 --> 01:13:03.040
Garner versus Tennessee, which
involved a very specific policy

01:13:03.040 --> 01:13:03.600
intervention.

01:13:03.600 --> 01:13:05.420
Anybody?

01:13:05.420 --> 01:13:09.640
Fleeing felon, fleeing
felon, not Miranda rights.

01:13:09.640 --> 01:13:13.060
Fleeing felon, before
Garner versus Tennessee,

01:13:13.060 --> 01:13:15.850
police used to do two things,
which were really bad.

01:13:15.850 --> 01:13:18.822
They used to fire
warning shots, not good.

01:13:18.822 --> 01:13:20.530
And they used to shoot
people in the back

01:13:20.530 --> 01:13:22.070
when they were running away.

01:13:22.070 --> 01:13:27.710
All right, so policies reduced,
after Garner versus Tennessee,

01:13:27.710 --> 01:13:29.710
that basically diffused
through police agencies,

01:13:29.710 --> 01:13:33.190
saw a massive drop in
police-involved shootings.

01:13:33.190 --> 01:13:35.260
In New York City alone,
it went from about 100

01:13:35.260 --> 01:13:39.100
to a year to about 10 a year
within a nine-year period,

01:13:39.100 --> 01:13:42.670
simply by instituting two
internal sorts of changes

01:13:42.670 --> 01:13:44.842
within the police department.

01:13:44.842 --> 01:13:47.300
All that said, I want to close
on the thing I started with,

01:13:47.300 --> 01:13:49.091
which is, look, you
didn't tell us anything

01:13:49.091 --> 01:13:50.560
about inequality and power.

01:13:50.560 --> 01:13:53.800
Well, right, because that's
what creates the networks.

01:13:53.800 --> 01:13:56.850
You know what's
really hard to do?

01:13:56.850 --> 01:13:57.980
Change networks.

01:13:57.980 --> 01:13:59.680
It's really hard
to change networks.

01:13:59.680 --> 01:14:00.910
It's like a highway system.

01:14:00.910 --> 01:14:02.481
Once you build it,
it's pernicious.

01:14:02.481 --> 01:14:02.980
It's hard.

01:14:02.980 --> 01:14:04.480
You don't have an off ramp here.

01:14:04.480 --> 01:14:05.616
You have one here.

01:14:05.616 --> 01:14:07.990
You can change the rules of
the road and the speed limits

01:14:07.990 --> 01:14:09.370
and improve safety in vehicles.

01:14:09.370 --> 01:14:11.720
We talked about that as an
effort of public health.

01:14:11.720 --> 01:14:13.250
We can start there.

01:14:13.250 --> 01:14:15.940
But ultimately, we have to
think about the ways which

01:14:15.940 --> 01:14:19.197
