01:14:31.660 --> 01:14:32.290
Correct?

01:14:32.290 --> 01:14:34.039
I'm talking about
high-rise public housing

01:14:34.039 --> 01:14:35.100
projects in particular.

01:14:35.100 --> 01:14:37.540
And Those were built in
particular times and places

01:14:37.540 --> 01:14:38.740
for particular reasons.

01:14:38.740 --> 01:14:41.590
I'm happy to go on about
some of these other dynamics.

01:14:41.590 --> 01:14:44.110
But really, we also have to
think about those big things.

01:14:44.110 --> 01:14:45.220
We have to think
about all the things

01:14:45.220 --> 01:14:46.928
that aren't going to
help the victims who

01:14:46.928 --> 01:14:50.140
are in those networks today and
were the red dots, but in fact

01:14:50.140 --> 01:14:51.220
sort of there other else.

01:14:51.220 --> 01:14:53.034
And the last bit
with the new work

01:14:53.034 --> 01:14:54.700
we're doing in New
Haven, is, of course,

01:14:54.700 --> 01:14:57.430
we're now going in there in
a mixed methods approach,

01:14:57.430 --> 01:14:58.970
not looking at
those who got shot,

01:14:58.970 --> 01:15:00.850
but those who seem
to be resilient.

01:15:00.850 --> 01:15:03.433
And we're doing a mixed methods
study where we're interviewing

01:15:03.433 --> 01:15:06.000
these individuals who by every
metric should have been shot,

01:15:06.000 --> 01:15:08.980
that are surrounded by
gunshot victims, and aren't.

01:15:08.980 --> 01:15:11.140
We're doing this with a
community based project,

01:15:11.140 --> 01:15:13.782
