01:17:20.030 --> 01:17:21.000
- Marcia Castro.

01:17:21.000 --> 01:17:23.810
So Dr. Kolodny, could
you say a little bit more

01:17:23.810 --> 01:17:27.210
why the opioid epidemic
is mainly among whites?

01:17:27.210 --> 01:17:30.420
- Sure, I'll share with
you my theory about why

01:17:30.420 --> 01:17:31.740
the epidemic is so white.

01:17:31.740 --> 01:17:35.520
And I think I showed you the
data, treatment admissions

01:17:35.520 --> 01:17:39.010
data, that showed you how
white the epidemic is.

01:17:39.010 --> 01:17:42.210
But if you look at the mortality
data, it's also very white.

01:17:42.210 --> 01:17:44.910
If you look at
hospital admissions,

01:17:44.910 --> 01:17:47.670
every way you look at
this, it's striking

01:17:47.670 --> 01:17:49.770
how white the epidemic is.

01:17:49.770 --> 01:17:52.290
What I believe is happening--
and this is a theory,

01:17:52.290 --> 01:17:54.580
but it's based on evidence.

01:17:54.580 --> 01:17:59.610
Something we do know is that
doctors prescribe narcotics

01:17:59.610 --> 01:18:03.060
more cautiously to
their nonwhite patients.

01:18:03.060 --> 01:18:06.780
If a patient is
black, the doctor

01:18:06.780 --> 01:18:09.289
prescribes opioids
much less frequently.

01:18:09.289 --> 01:18:11.080
It would seem that if
the patient is black,

01:18:11.080 --> 01:18:14.250
the doctor may be more worried
about the patient becoming

01:18:14.250 --> 01:18:16.200
addicted, or maybe
they're more worried

01:18:16.200 --> 01:18:18.960
about the patient
selling their pills.

01:18:18.960 --> 01:18:20.460
And if the patient
is white, they're

01:18:20.460 --> 01:18:24.347
prescribing as if there's
nothing to worry about.

01:18:24.347 --> 01:18:26.430
And of course, we should
be prescribing cautiously

01:18:26.430 --> 01:18:27.610
to all of our patients.

01:18:27.610 --> 01:18:32.130
So that the black patient
is less likely to wind up

01:18:32.130 --> 01:18:34.350
getting addicted to
medicine prescribed to them,

01:18:34.350 --> 01:18:38.130
and the black household
is less likely to have

01:18:38.130 --> 01:18:40.200
a highly addictive drug
in the medicine chest.

01:18:40.200 --> 01:18:42.510
So what I believe
is happening is

01:18:42.510 --> 01:18:47.520
that racial stereotyping is
having a protective effect

01:18:47.520 --> 01:18:50.220
on nonwhite populations.

01:18:50.220 --> 01:18:52.320
- If I may, framing
it another way,

01:18:52.320 --> 01:18:56.280
is it possible then because the
argument the industry would use

01:18:56.280 --> 01:19:00.210
is that possible pain
management is not

01:19:00.210 --> 01:19:05.080
equally met, as well addressed
for nonwhite populations?

01:19:05.080 --> 01:19:05.580
- Yes.

01:19:05.580 --> 01:19:06.540
- Are there evidence?

01:19:06.540 --> 01:19:08.160
- There is.

01:19:08.160 --> 01:19:10.920
And so, in fact,
some of the studies

01:19:10.920 --> 01:19:15.300
that proved that doctors
prescribe narcotics

01:19:15.300 --> 01:19:17.930
less frequently to
their nonwhite patients

01:19:17.930 --> 01:19:20.160
were sponsored by
pharmaceutical companies that

01:19:20.160 --> 01:19:22.380
were trying to get the
prescribing to go up

01:19:22.380 --> 01:19:24.280
for nonwhite populations.

01:19:24.280 --> 01:19:27.090
So the argument has
been made that we're

01:19:27.090 --> 01:19:30.140
under treating
pain in non-whites

01:19:30.140 --> 01:19:31.890
or African-Americans.

01:19:31.890 --> 01:19:34.630
The problem is that opioids
are very good medicines

01:19:34.630 --> 01:19:35.640
for palliative care.

01:19:35.640 --> 01:19:36.990
And I think they are--

01:19:36.990 --> 01:19:40.060
I would hope that they are
prescribed more appropriately.

01:19:40.060 --> 01:19:43.535
If they're not prescribed
to black patients

01:19:43.535 --> 01:19:44.910
in palliative care
settings, that

01:19:44.910 --> 01:19:46.530
would be very inappropriate.

01:19:46.530 --> 01:19:51.000
And there is the
possibility that we

01:19:51.000 --> 01:19:53.906
are under prescribing opioids
in cases where we should.

01:19:53.906 --> 01:19:55.530
But overall, I think
that's why they've

01:19:55.530 --> 01:19:57.290
been spared the epidemic.

